records.addlTxt:
Defendant Robert Leon Harris in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by the state, defense, Donald R., Keith T., and defendant. 

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 45 MONTHS, CONSECUTIVE any other time being served with credit for 3 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 30 MONTHS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment- if necessary complete follow-up treatment-take prescription meds only in the manner as prescribed by treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment- complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety- random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers/houses);
*Cooperate with all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment OR if enrolled in school full time, part time work;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*No Contact with Stephen T.;  
*Perform 50 hours of community service (under supervision,no compensation);

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court orders restitution in the stipulated amount of $2,819.00 payable to Stephen T.- to be paid first.  The Court ordered defendant to pay all mandatory costs, penalties, surcharges, including $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge. Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan; cooperate with any treatment recommended.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 24 months.  Court ordered defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 18 months.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.
Filed;
